    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="transcription">
                <pb n="1" facs="00000219.jpg"/>
                <note type="foliation" hand="#pencil_1"
                    place="top-right"><del rend="strikethrough" hand="#pencil_2">120</del></note>
                <note type="foliation" hand="#blue_hand" place="top-right">103</note>
                <p><address><addrLine rend="align(center)"><hi rend="large"><rs ref="#p0572">Decano</rs> &amp; <orgName ref="#g0028">Facultati philosophicae</orgName></hi></addrLine><addrLine rend="align(center)">summe venerandis.<note resp="#eva.schneider">Bei diesem und folgendem Dokument handelt es sich um das Promotionsgesuch von <persName ref="#p0662">Immanuel Hermann Fichte</persName>, das er im November 1817 an der <orgName ref="#g0137">Philosophischen Fakultät</orgName> der <orgName ref="#g0122">Berliner Universität</orgName> einreichte. Es bestand aus einem Gesuch und einem Lebenslauf mit einer Übersicht über seine bisherige Studien.</note></addrLine></address></p>
                <p>Cum indulgentiae Vestrae non sine timore hancce dissertationem trado,<lb/> ut ex
                    ea iudicare Vobis placeat, <unclear cert="low" reason="illegible">ea</unclear>
                    dignus sim, qui ad tentamen<lb/> Doctoris Philosophiae admittar: libere
                    confiteor, me ipsum mi<lb break="no"/>nime esse <add place="above"
                        >contentum</add> opusculo meo, &amp;, nisi defuisset tempus, alia sultem
                        for<lb break="no"/>ma iudicio Vestro illud oblaturum fuisse. Nihil enim,
                    nisi<lb/> partem dissertationis, quam antea examini subiicere volue<lb
                        break="no"/>ram, tradere licet, eamque &amp; <choice>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high">ea</unclear>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low">quae</unclear>
                    </choice> materia &amp; forma imper<lb break="no"/>fectam: ceterorum, quae
                    retinui, argumentum brevi coropectu<lb/> Vobis proposui. <unclear
                        reason="illegible" cert="high">T</unclear>am igitur Vestrum <add
                        place="above">erit</add>, spectare non quid fece<lb break="no"/>rit auctor,
                    sed quid facere voluerit. &#8211; Omnino autem in<lb/> philosophia a provectiore
                        <add place="above">demum</add> &amp; firmata aetate, atque post<lb/> multas
                    variasque exercitationes, probi ac perfecti quid ex<lb break="no"/>spectari
                    potest; illam nondum nactus sum, his adhuc<lb/> careo. Specimini igitur sit,
                        <add place="above">quod porrigo</add>, <choice>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high">an</unclear>
                        <unclear reason="illigible" cert="low">un</unclear>
                    </choice>
                    <hi rend="underline">futuro</hi> tempore litteris ali<lb break="no"/>qua tenus
                    profuturum me sperare possim. Sed quid pluribus<lb/> opus est! Sum&#772;a
                    fiducia se suuque Vestrae commendat indul<lb break="no"/>gentiae.</p>
                <closer><choice>
                        <abbr>Scrib.</abbr>
                        <expan>Scriba</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <placeName ref="#l1103">Berolini</placeName>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>d.</abbr>
                        <expan>der</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <date when-iso="1817-11-13">13 <choice>
                            <abbr>Novembr.</abbr>
                            <expan>November</expan>
                        </choice> 1817</date>. <hi rend="align(right)">devotus
                            discipulus<lb/><persName ref="#p0662"><signed>Imanuelis
                            Fichte</signed></persName>.</hi></closer>
                <p><hi rend="underline align(right)">verte</hi></p>
                <p>
                    <handShift new="#minor_hand"/>
                    <hi rend="kurrent">Als Parthei trete ich in dieser Sache <unclear
                            reason="illegible" cert="high">zugleich</unclear> ab! Ich freue mich
                        aufrichtig, wen&#772; die <orgName ref="#g0028">Fakultät</orgName><lb/> von
                        der Weissheit der Schrift sich überzeugt hat. Mein Lob der Schrift, selbst
                        habe ich bereits<lb/> auf das stärkste ausgesprochen. Hat sie einen so jungen
                        Verfaßer &#8211; wohl uns und ihm!</hi> &#8211; <persName ref="#p0613">
                            <signed>Weiss</signed></persName>.</p>

                <pb n="2" facs="00000220.jpg"/>
                <note type="foliation" hand="#ink" place="top">86.</note> 
                <note type="foliation" hand="#pencil_3" place="margin-left-vertical">36</note>
                
                
                <pb n="3" facs="00000221.jpg"/>
                <note type="foliation" hand="blue_hand" place="top-right">104</note>
                <handShift new="#major_hand"/>
                <p>Quae de vita hucusque peracta dicenda mihi sunt, brevibus<lb/> absolveri possum.
                    &#8211; Natus sum <placeName ref="#l0100">Jenae</placeName>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>a.D.</abbr>
                        <expan>Anno Domini</expan>
                    </choice>
                    <date when-iso="1796">MDCCXCVI</date>,<lb/> ubi <rs ref="#p0251">pater</rs> meus
                    munere doctoris academici fungebatur. Cum<lb/> parentibus mox <placeName
                        ref="#l1103">Berolinum</placeName>
                    <choice>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high">profectus</unclear>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low">praefectus</unclear>
                    </choice>, ibi omnibus iis sum<lb/> eruditus, quae decent puerum honestum,
                    partim <choice>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high">privates</unclear>
                        <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low">privatis</unclear>
                    </choice> stu<lb break="no"/>diis, cum patris ipsius, optimi disciplina
                    gauderem, partim<lb/> in publicis urbis nostrae lyceis. Deinde, cum tempus ad<lb
                        break="no"/>esset, quo iam in Academia eruditio esset persequenda, <orgName
                        ref="#g0122">Univer<lb break="no"/>sitatis</orgName> nostrae cives factus,
                    ad antiquas litteras me conver<lb break="no"/>ti, &amp; disciplinis Virorum
                    Clariss. <persName ref="#p0175">Wolfii</persName>, <persName ref="#p0146"
                        >Solgeri</persName>, <persName ref="#p0178">Boe<lb break="no"
                        />ckhii</persName>, <persName ref="#p0624">Ideleri</persName> me commisi:
                    per triennium etiam <orgName ref="#g0079">Se<lb break="no"/>minarii
                        Philologici</orgName> sodalis, non possum, quin impri<lb break="no"/>mis
                        <persName ref="#p0178">Boeckhio</persName> &amp; <persName ref="#p0394"
                        >Buttmanno</persName>, celeberrimis eius <orgName ref="#g0079"
                        >instituti</orgName><lb/> moderatoribus &amp; praeceptoribus meis pie
                    colendis, intimo<lb/> ex animo gratias agam propter multa &amp; varia,
                    quibus<lb/> mihi profuerunt. &#8211; Mox, antiquas litteras relinquens, per<lb/>
                    triennium fere privato studio philosophiae totis viribus<lb/> operam dedi.<lb/>
                <milestone unit="none" rend="horizontal-rule" n="2"/>    
                
                    <pb n="4" facs="00000222.jpg"/>
                    <note type="foliation" hand="#ink" place="top">86<hi rend="superscript latin">a</hi></note>
                    <note type="foliation" hand="#pencil_3" place="margin-left-vertical">35</note>
                        
                </p>
